description: Spyro 2 is a game about a purple dragon who wants to go on vacation.

0.1.0.description:
# Spyro 2 - Ripto's Rage (1999) - Archipelago Implementation v0.1.0

This is the initial alpha/unstable release of an APWorld and Client for Spyro 2 for PSX. This supports only NTSC-U (US release) of the original game and requires Windows and Duckstation to play.

Release: https://github.com/Uroogla/S2AP/releases/tag/0.1.0
Setup and Requirements: https://github.com/Uroogla/S2AP/blob/main/README.md

## What Checks are Supported?
- All 14 talismans
- All 64 Orbs
- 25%, 50%, 75%, and/or 100% of gems in each level (optional)
- Every 500 total gems, to a user specified maximum (optional)
- Skill Points (optional)

## What Goals are Possible?
- Defeat Ripto with 40+ orbs (default)
- Defeat Ripto with 14 talismans, regardless of orb count
- Defeat Ripto by any means possible
- Defeat Ripto with all 64 orbs
- Defeat Ripto with 10000 gems, 64 orbs, and 14 talismans
- Obtain all 10 Dragon Shores tokens
- Obtain all 16 skill points
- Complete the epilogue by defeating Ripto and obtaining all 16 skill points

## What's in the Item Pool?
- 6 Summer Forest Talismans (not tied to individual levels).  All 6 required to enter Crush in logic.
- 8 Autumn Plains Talismans (not tied to individual levels).  All 14 talismans required to enter Gulp in logic.
- 64 Orbs (not tied to individual challenges)
- Moneybags Unlocks (optional)
- Progressive Sparx Health Upgrades, allowing you to start with lower max HP for a challenge (optional)
- Permanent Fireball Ability (optional)
- Double Jump Ability (optional)
- Miscellaneous Fun/Helpful Items (pick which to include)
  - Extra Lives
  - Sparx Heal
  - Change Spyro's Color
  - Big Head Mode and Flat Spyro Mode
- Miscellaneous Traps (pick which to include)
  - Sparx Damage Trap
  - Sparxless Trap
  - Temporary Invisible Spyro Trap

## Known Bugs
- There may be occasional missyncs between the client and server (off by 1 item issue).  Typing `clearSpyroGameState` into the client and following its instructions will generally fix this.

## Are There Custom Client Commands?
- `clearSpyroGameState` Resync your save file's received items with the server in case of a desync.  This may result in duplicate filler items.
If playing on a new save file, you will still need to finish Glimmer and beat Crush and Gulp to proceed.
- `showTalismanCount` Prints how many Summer Forest Talisman items and how many Autumn Plains Talisman items the player has received.
- `useQuietHints` Suppresses hints for found locations to make the client easier to read. On by default.
- `useVerboseHints` Include found locations in hint lists. Due to Archipelago Server limitations, only applies to hints requested after this change.

0.1.2.description:
More Aquaria Towers logic fixes (removes potentially required permanent fireball or sheep proxy).

This update does NOT require a new client; the 0.1.1 client will continue to work.

0.2.0.description:
NOTE: This release had a significant error for non-gemsanity playthroughs and has been superseded by version 0.2.1.

This release is not backwards compatible (cannot be used with seeds from previous versions).

Changes:
- Bugfixes
  - Fix logic for Summer Forest climb orb, Magma Cone total gems, and Winter Tundra total gems.
  - Fix Big Head Mode
  - Fix issue where some items might not fully register on being received.
- QoL improvements
  - When you receive a talisman, the client with show how many you have.
  - Talking to Elora outside Crush and Gulp will tell you how many talismans you have, if you don't have enough.
  - The client will print your goal on connect; useful for random settings.
- Add Destructive Spyro filler item.  Anything breakable or defeatable will be broken/defeated when Spyro runs into it, for a short time.
- Add Life Bottles as Checks
- Add Partial Gemsanity, which makes 200 random gems into checks and adds 8 "50 gem" items for each level with loose gems in it.  This feature is in alpha, use at your own risk.

Known Issues:
- Client may display an error that it could not write to DataStorage if you receive an item at the same time it is writing.  As long as this message doesn't repeat every minute, this is fine.
- During Gemsanity, entering a level or respawning on death may play a beeping noise.  This is *technically* vanilla behavior.
- Loading into a save during Gemsanity may release a few extra checks, based on what gems you've collected so far.
- Some users have reported checks sending when connecting to the server at the loading screen or when resetting Duckstation.  To avoid this, connect to the server when in game, and close the client before resetting.
0.2.0.title: [DEPRECATED] 0.2.0

0.2.1.description:
Fixes a bug where gems would regularly reset to 0 when gemsanity was turned off.

No change to .apworld is needed.  If you encountered this bug, use the new client and revisit levels where you previously collected gems.  The in game count will fix itself as you do so.  Apologies for the inconvenience!

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/Uroogla/S2AP/compare/0.2.0...0.2.1

0.2.2.description:
This release patches a couple of potential errors and crashes when reconnecting to an async.

The .apworld is unchanged from the previous release.

0.3.0.description:
While this client should be compatible with 0.2.x, I recommend using it only with 0.3.0.

Spyro 2 for Archipelago is still in alpha, meaning there are a few known issues that could negatively impact a multiworld experience.

Additions:
- Open World mode with level (un)locks.
- Added all spirit particles in a level as a check.
- Add option to start with fireball.
- The first of hopefully many cosmetic randomizer effects.
- Warns if not running in admin mode, tries to always run in admin mode.

Bug fixes:
- Fixed bug where Glimmer marked the wrong gems as climb-locked.
- Progressive Client Stability Improvement.

 Known issues:
- When settings are valid, failed to generate seeds roughly 0.03% of the time. These tend to be when total gem checks are on with a high number.  This might indicate a minor logic error.
- If resetting Duckstation or save-quitting out of the game, restart the client when re-entering the game.  Otherwise, level locks and cosmetic effects will not work.
- Loading into a save during Gemsanity may release a few extra checks, based on what gems you've collected so far.
- Some users have reported checks sending when connecting to the server at the loading screen or when resetting Duckstation. To avoid this, connect to the server when in game, and close the client before resetting.
- Universal Tracker won’t show all gems in logic during partial gemsanity.
- Leaving the client and game idle for extended periods of time may result in error messages.
0.3.0.title: [DEPRECATED] 0.3.0

0.3.1.description:
Changes:
- Fixes bug where spirit particle checks were not tied to the corresponding option.
- Forces Swim to be in an early sphere to reduce restrictive start errors.

0.3.2.description:
This release modifies both the APWorld and the client.

Bug Fixes:
- Fixes an issue where orb count could become desynced if completing an orb check that has been collected by another player or sent by the host.
- Fixes an issue where resetting Duckstation could cause issues with open world mode level locks.
- Fixes an issue where 2 gems in Summer Forest had the wrong access restrictions.
- Fixes a typo in an option.

As of 16 November, 2025, this contains a patch to the client fixing a few bugs.
- Removes the beep that played when spawning during gemsanity
- Handles an edge case where the player closes Duckstation and then clicks the connect button again
- Prevents completing locations/sending checks when in the BIOS load, or using the PAL/NTSC-J version of S2.

1.0.0.description:
This release modifies both the APWorld and the client.  When Archipelago version 0.7.0 is eventually released,
this will be the earliest version of Spyro 2 to be supported.

Features:
- Client flags if host's APWorld is out of date
- Customizable door to the final boss
- "Normal Spyro" filler item, undoing other cosmetic filler items
- Options for easier orb challenges
- Allows players to do headbash orb challenges with fireball instead of headbash (not in logic)
- Gem and orb color randomizer
- Deathlink

Changes:
- Improved Universal Tracker support
- Changed goal system
- Temporarily remove early boss logic
- Level Lock even without Open World mode

Bug Fixes:
- Fixes minor logic bugs
- Fixes a bug with Item Links
- Fixes a bug with the 100% goal when gemsanity is off.
- Prevents (again) completing locations/sending checks when in the BIOS load.

Note: Patched a minor Universal Tracker issue an hour after release.

1.0.1.description:
This release modifies both the APWorld and the client.  The new client will work with seeds in progress that were rolled with APWorld 1.0.0, but it is recommended to update your APWorld for new seeds.

Changes:
- Progressive Client Improvements (enter to send message, autoscroll on by default, menu bug) - thanks to ArsonAssassin for the package update!
- Updated memory library, hopefully reducing memory leaks.

Bug Fixes:
- Fixed most cases where DeathLink did not trigger on death, and one case where it triggered on loading a save.
- Fixed small logic bugs around gem availability.  Primarily impacts trackers rather than in game experience.
- Fixed bug where saving in Winter Tundra corrupted players' save files and released specific orb checks on reconnect.

1.0.2.description:
This release modifies only the client, which will work with APWorld version 1.0.1.  An APWorld with a new version number is provided for convenience but is not required.

Bug Fixes:
- Fixed bugs that could cause a crash on connect or goal completion.

1.1.0.description:
This release modifies both the client (S2AP.Desktop.exe) and the APWorld.  The client will largely work with seeds in progress, though Summer Forest gem 46 may be logically required without swim, despite requiring it in practice.

New Features:
- Full Gemsanity Beta
  - Full Gemsanity makes every gem a check but the gem items are all local.  Full Global makes every gem a check with no restrictions on the location of gem items.
  - For games with more than 1 player, these settings require host approval via the allow_full_gemsanity setting in the Spyro 2 section of the host.yaml file.  This setting has a substantial impact on generation times (adding 2546 progression items) and can send frequent messages to everyone's client, so not every host will allow these settings.

Bug fixes:
- Fixed the indices of 3 gems in Summer Forest and 1 gem in Fracture Hills.
- Removed (again) the beep sound that played when spawning into a level with Gemsanity on.
- For better performance and reduced crash chances, gemsanity checks will only trigger while you are in the same level as the gem.
  - This means that if you collect gems while not connected to the server, you will need to return to the level to trigger the corresponding checks.
  - This should have no impact on normal gameplay.
1.1.0.title: v1.1.0

1.1.1.description:
This release contains changes only to the client (S2AP.Desktop.exe).  The APWorld remains unchanged - a copy with an updated version number is provided for convenience, but seeds rolled on 1.1.0 will run correctly.

Bug Fix:
- Fixed a bug where if a player's most recent save is an autosave while exiting a Winter Tundra sublevel, the orb section of the save file became corrupted.
  - This bug existed on versions 1.0.0 and later.  If you are playing on the 1.0.1 or 1.0.2 client and cannot update, you can avoid this issue by ending with a manual save, or by using save states.
1.1.1.title: v1.1.1
